  • displacement vs acceleration - strong negative relationship

  • horsepower vs acceleration - strong negative relationship

### F)Suppose that we wish to predict gas mileage (mpg) on the basis of the other variables. Do your plots suggest that any of the other variables might be useful in predicting mpg? Justify your answer

par(mfrow=c(2,2))
plot(auto$mpg,auto$displacement)
plot(auto$mpg,auto$horsepower)
plot(auto$mpg,auto$weight)
plot(auto$mpg,auto$acceleration)

* mpg has strong negative relationship with displacement,horsepower and weight. * mpg moves in opposite direction of displacement,horsepower and weight. we can use these three predictor to predict mpg,if these three predictor is increasing mpg will be opposite of this predictors.

  • Also mpg has weak positve relationship with acceleration which is not useful for predicting
